The paper focuses on identifying and mitigating security vulnerabilities in Android Inter-Component Communication (ICC), which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents a static analysis tool that analyzes the code under development, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to study the prevalence of security code smells in open-source apps, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
